GM 🧵

I’ve been receiving a lot of accolades and props since I posted the letter.

Thank you.

Those cards did not get proofed, re-proofed, formatted, catalogued, organized, printed, inserted into sleeves in custom expensive leather bound binders , packaged and shipped all by me. 

@coloali bought me a laptop to make our work more efficient, paid for the binders shipping, set up a house and filled it with food for our binder building party and is still stealthily helping behind the scenes 

@backtobasixmom has helped with almost every aspect of the project donated money to keep a roof over my head and flew out on her own dime to help build binders. Donna is also still helping behind the scenes and is releasing “your favorite verse” and The Bible series

@zzgypsy0327 also gave me funds I know for a fact she can’t really afford and was the first one to message me and tell me she sees Gods hands working  through us in this project. Z is also helping behind the scenes, capturing your requests,helping find cards and whatever else needs doing

@BrunoSamar1717 procured the sleeves, binders and most importantly most of the funding for the first binders to be sent to DC

@AstuteActual has helped proofread,helped spread the word and find patriots on Truth social & post cards

@ChonitaNot has been a proofreader extraordinaire and put in lots of hours during “crunch time”

@NunyaBidnass0_o has been another proofreading stalwart and is patiently waiting in the wings for MOAR

@CreateUrTruth volunteered from day one, has helped proofread, logistically and had the idea for the fantastic Q chronological series which she is now releasing daily

@SPatriot61 is a long time friend who also volunteered early, has helped tremendously and is now dropping the cards for one of our most popular series “ your favorite drop”

@kewlbeings was instrumental in getting the Rubio series going and helped with proofreading Kewl has had some personal issues as of late it would be great if we could all keep her in our prayers

@Sense0fMeme17 jumped on board early to volunteer making videos of the cards we create if you aren’t following him please do because his videos are awesome

@DonnaWr34914422 another awesome Anon that’s been in the trenches for years graciously volunteered to tag all of your cards after I drop them she tags them one by one for you  in case you missed a drop

Our buddy @DickieT863 also helped with proofreading and is now releasing the Culper Spy Ring  series and if I can twist his arm enough will be releasing the sons of liberty series next

@Patriot777_  Courtney helped with proofreading, spreading the word on homebase - AU, and helped release some cards there

@buffiedawnmarie helped with proofreading but also had some family issues that took her away for the most part let’s please keep her in our prayers as well

I would be remiss if I did not thank @ScottZPatriot for his encouragement, his help with getting donations to get the podcast studio set up and of course for the offer for me to cohost a podcast to tell your stories

Shock Jock @JaredBasso gave us a platform on primetime mainstream AM radio to talk about the All-Stars for three weeks in a row!

A special shout-out to @WenBeck5 She volunteered early and was on the team. I had a bit of a conflict and asked her to kindly step aside. She graciously did and has supported the entire time

So many of you have quietly helped simply by sharing, liking and encouraging me to keep going. 

The donations have allowed me to focus on this labor of love and to, God willing, turning it into something more and I simply don’t have the words other than thank you. 

The personalized gifts I continue to receive blow me away and are so touching

I now have thousands of messages. DM’s , emails, messages on Buy Me a Coffee, text messages and phone calls about your journeys in this silent war and incredible words of encouragement 

The Anon All Stars is a miracle in my life.

Than You❤️

Some alpha on what im focused on for the rest of 2026 across AI plays

Global AI spend is hitting $2.59T this year, up 47% YoY. Capital is pricing every layer of the stack already.

– agent software: $206.5B this year → $376.3B in 2027
– agentic AI growing 141% in 2026, fastest line in enterprise IT budgets
– AI-native agent platforms getting 14–22x rev multiples, sometimes 20–30x private
– 266 AI M&A deals in Q1 alone, up ~90% YoY

This is also why I think inference is the real AI trade going into H2.

Inference already accounts for ~2/3 of AI compute and somewhere between 55–80% of enterprise GPU spend.

Coding agents, research agents, search, customer support, robotics and background workflows do not consume one inference call.

They sit there thinking, retrying, calling tools, checking results and talking to other agents all day.

Cost per token drops, total token demand goes vertical. So inference prints every time the model works

Crypto AI actually fits this narrative.

– @AskVenice: serving 3M+ users with anonymous access to frontier and open models, TEE/E2EE privacy, agentic chat and x402 payments.

– @chutes_ai: decentralized training via Parallax, full inference stack into TEEs, Blackwell B200/B300 capacity added, enclave cold starts cut ~20x.

@ionet: 4B+ AI tokens/day, 30M+ compute hours, ~$12M ARR. decentralized GPUs running production-scale inference is no longer a maybe.

@akashnet: pushed decentralized inference into real production scale, 100B+ tokens processed in april, 5B+ tokens/day avg, 7B daily peak.

@rendernetwork: pushed Dispersed deeper into AI inference with Windows and global onboarding, cloud storage integrations, live MCP support and real AI workloads.

Once agents become long-lived workers, persistent memory becomes a first-class primitive right next to inference.

Crypto has a real edge here with portable identity, permissioned data ownership, auditable memory.

@0G_labs: stores encrypted agent memory on decentralized storage, anchors ownership through Agentic ID and re-keys memory when ownership is transferred.

@irys_xyz: building a programmable datachain for AI memory, shipping ~20% faster block validation and VDF cycles, stronger load resilience, faster node recovery and safer data retrieval.

@recallnet: its memory layer records agent actions, reasoning traces and state transitions onchain, turning past performance into auditable history and reputation.

@Unibase_AI: launching BitAgent with ChainGPT and RoboPay integrations while recording agent requests, execution and settlement into Membase as persistent, verifiable history.

@billions_ntwk: building a trust layer for AI memory with portable agent identity, owner linkage, permissions and verifiable provenance, so persistent memory and actions can be attributed and audited.

Robotics is the other narrative i wouldnt sleep on for H2

April saw ~$3.2B disclosed across 109 robotics rounds. Robotics multiplies every AI bottleneck crypto is already solving

@GEODNET: 22K+ RTK stations across 150+ countries, powering cm-level positioning for Burro robots, autonomous drone systems, peaqOS machines and outdoor fleets.

@peaq: shipped peaqOS V1 in Q2, activating 205 machines with onchain identities, wallets, credit ratings, autonomous service payments and verifiable data.

@xmaquina: expanded DAO exposure across Figure AI, Apptronik, Sanctuary AI, 1X, Agility, NEURA and Genki Robotics.

@StrikeRobot_ai: proving real sim-to-real deployment, expanding into multi-robot and on-device edge inference, then shipping SR Platform with native MuJoCo and Isaac Sim support.

@codecopenflow: shipped SimArena, where builders can create scenes, collect demos, train policies in the browser and export to Isaac Sim, MuJoCo or LeRobot.

Q2 taught us the AI stack has way more scarce layers than just the model.

Everything required to run intelligence continuously is becoming the new scarce asset.
